etymologies: late 19th century: from dialysis+ -ate; the term originally denoted the part of the mixture which does not pass through the membrane

definitions: the part of a mixture which passes through the membrane in dialysis.
shortDefinitions: part of mixture which passes through membrane in dialysis

definitions: the solution dialyzate forms with the fluid on the other side of the membrane in dialysis.
shortDefinitions: solution dialysate forms with fluid on other side of membrane

definitions: the fluid used on the other side of the membrane during dialysis to remove impurities.
shortDefinitions: fluid used on other side of membrane during dialysis
